## üéØ Clinical Applications

### Primary Pattern & Manifestations
**Pattern**: Blood stasis with underlying yang deficiency and dampness
**Key Symptoms**: Irregular menstruation, dysmenorrhea, uterine masses, abdominal masses, chronic pelvic pain, dark menstrual blood with clots, cold hands and feet
**Tongue**: Purple or with purple spots, may have white coating
**Pulse**: Wiry and choppy, or deep and choppy

### Secondary Applications
- Uterine fibroids and ovarian cysts
- Endometriosis and adenomyosis
- Chronic pelvic inflammatory disease
- Infertility due to blood stasis
- Menopausal symptoms with masses
- Chronic hepatitis with liver enlargement

### Modern Clinical Uses
- Gynecological conditions with blood stasis
- Uterine fibroids and benign ovarian masses
- Endometriosis and chronic pelvic pain
- Infertility treatments (blood stasis type)
- Menopausal transition symptoms
- Autoimmune conditions with circulation issues

## üìù Therapeutic Actions
**Primary**: Warm yang qi, move blood, resolve stasis, regulate menstruation

**Secondary**: Reduce inflammation, dissolve masses, improve circulation, regulate hormones

